.TH mlib_ImageSqrShift_Inp 3MLIB "2 Mar 2007" "SunOS 5.11" "mediaLib Library Functions"
.SH NAME
mlib_ImageSqrShift_Inp \- square with shifting, in place
.SH SYNOPSIS
.LP
.nf
cc [ \fIflag\fR.\|.\|. ] \fIfile\fR.\|.\|. \fB-lmlib\fR [ \fIlibrary\fR.\|.\|. ]
#include <mlib.h>

\fBmlib_status\fR \fBmlib_ImageSqrShift_Inp\fR(\fBmlib_image *\fIsrcdst\fR, \fBmlib_s32\fR \fIshift\fR);
.fi

.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
.LP
The \fBmlib_ImageSqrShift_Inp()\fR function computes the square of each
pixel in the source image and scales the result by the shift factor, in
place.
.sp
.LP
It uses the following equation:
.sp
.in +2
.nf
srcdst[x][y][i] = srcdst[x][y][i] * srcdst[x][y][i] * 2**(-shift)
.fi
.in -2

.SH PARAMETERS
.sp
.LP
The function takes the following arguments:
.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
.I srcdst
.ad
.RS 10n
.rt
Pointer to source and destination image.
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
\fIshift\fR
.ad
.RS 10n
.rt
Right shifting factor. \fB0 \(<= shift \(<= 31\fR.
.RE

.SH RETURN VALUES
.sp
.LP
The function returns
.B MLIB_SUCCESS
if successful. Otherwise it returns
.BR MLIB_FAILURE .
